      "writtenOn": "2026-04-27T14:25:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Noting our conversation from earlier here. The plan as proposed means that Go dependency resolution is dependent on VCS. This is a risk we need to call out and quantify to my mind, because \"regular\" Go dependency resolution from a consumer perspective does not depend on VCS. Either at all (if the module publish uses the `mod` VCS type) or in the extremely limited case of a consumer being the first person to ask a VCS-backed proxy for a version the proxy hasn\u0027t seen. This proposal as I understand it has _every_ consumer of a CUE+Go co-located module relying on VCS.",
      "revId": "a111bd4e11dbefbbd5d640fa18cced4c309c05a3",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
